- OpenSats Issues Long-Term Support Grant to Bruno Garcia [Opensats] (https://opensats.org/blog/bruno-garcia-receives-lts-grant)
 - Bruno Garcia, a Brazilian developer, receives long-term support from an organization due to his significant contributions to Bitcoin Core.
 - Garcia began contributing to Bitcoin Core in 2021 after being inspired by Brazil's economic crisis in the '90s.
 - His work includes fixing bugs, implementing new features, and enhancing the Bitcoin network's resilience.
 - He created bitcoinfuzz, a crucial tool for identifying issues within Bitcoin libraries and implementations.
 - Additionally, Garcia works on ASMap, which aims to strengthen the Bitcoin network by promoting diverse node connections.
 - Beyond technical contributions, Garcia mentors aspiring Bitcoin developers through initiatives like the Summer of Bitcoin.
 - Funding from the grant will enable Garcia to continue his work while maintaining his focus on the long term.


### Software Releases & Project Updates
- Samourai Launches Stage 1 of Whirlpool Decentralization [Twitter Announcement] (https://twitter.com/SamouraiWallet/status/1770560344865267954)
 - Samourai has launched the initial phase of decentralizing its Whirlpool coinjoin service.
 - Updates were rolled out for Samourai Wallet, Whirlpool GUI/CLI, and Dojo, enabling decentralized Whirlpool usage.
 - Communication between Whirlpool clients and coordinators is now facilitated via the Soroban network, ensuring continuity even when servers go offline.
 - Users are encouraged to update their software to take advantage of these improvements.
 - Further stages involve incorporating multiple coordinators for enhanced decentralization.
 - In the future, users may operate their own Soroban nodes to contribute to the system's robustness.
 - More details about the updated services will be provided in upcoming guides and announcements. - 
- RoboSats v0.6.0-alpha: The Federation Layer [Github](https://github.com/RoboSats/robosats/releases/tag/v0.6.0-alpha)
 - RoboSats v0.6.0-alpha introduces the Federation Layer, which allows multiple RoboSats instances to function as a single entity through a unified client application.
 - This feature improves the platform's resilience and user experience while maintaining transparency and security.
 - Decentralization is achieved through the use of independent coordinators hosting orders.
 - A new avatar generator creates unique identities within the client app, improving speed and appearance.
 - Bug fixes and performance enhancements have been implemented throughout the application.
- (New Release) Stratum V2 Reference Implementation (SRI) v1.0.0 [Twitter Announcement](https://twitter.com/StratumV2/status/1770937873111331309) 
 - Aims to improve efficiency, security, flexibility, and decentralization in bitcoin mining.
 - Fully open-source and community-driven: Independent of any single entity and aims to be fully compatible with Stratum V2 Specification.
 - Enhanced features include: Connectivity to SV2 Pools, optional local job declaration client usage, and patched Bitcoin Core Node for creating custom block templates.
 - Code refactoring introduces the ability for nodes and JDC to be run by independent third parties, promoting transparency and accountability among pool operators.
 - Newly added pool fallback functionality helps ensure miners have multiple options when connecting to pools, reducing reliance on individual pools and encouraging competition.
 - The project welcomes contributions from developers and encourages individuals and corporations to support its development and maintenance.
- UmbrelOS v1.0: New UI, Architectural Overhaul, Search & More [Github] (https://github.com/getumbrel/umbrel/releases/tag/v1.0.0)
 - Available for Raspberry Pi 4, Pi 5, and Umbrel Home devices.
 - Linux users can expect an update in April 2024.
 - New UI: Visually appealing, easy to navigate, and customizable with widgets.
 - Search feature: Instantly locate system settings, apps, or initiate actions using a keyboard shortcut.
 - Quick Actions: Interact with apps and system settings quickly through right-click shortcuts.
 - Architectural overhaul: Improves stability, speed, and simplifies the overall experience.
 - Live Usage: Monitor real-time device performance metrics such as storage, memory, and CPU usage.
 - Multilingual support: Choose from eight different system languages.
- (New Release) Bitcoin Mints [Nostr Announcement] (https://primal.net/e/note1hxq7ey2hpmqxzwtlua48kdg97huukgrckn8p0n9ht7pppaxc2daqvu7c5a)
 - Launch of BitcoinMints.com: First platform listing and reviewing Cashu mints, utilizing Nostr as its discovery and identity layer.
 - Enables MakePrisms.com users to send millions of bitcoin transactions with a single click.
 - Utilizes NIP-87 to publish and review mints, providing a decentralized solution for listing and evaluating Cashu mints.
- Strike Black [Website] (https://strike.me/black/)
 -Strike BLACK offers comprehensive tools for integrating Bitcoin services into apps.
 - Services include buying, selling, and holding bitcoin; sending and receiving payments via Bitcoin or Lightning; connecting cash payment methods; making cash payouts to bank accounts; onboarding through KYC flows; and utilizing OAuth for authentication, permissions, and access controls.
 - Strike BLACK provides flexibility and customization options, allowing users to choose which services to implement and how to deliver them to end-users.
 - Users can integrate Strike BLACK's services either programmatically via the Strike API or through the in-app Strike widget.
 - By offering a wide range of Bitcoin-related functionalities, Strike BLACK aims to provide a complete solution for developers looking to incorporate Bitcoin features into their applications.
- (New Release) Open Agents:  https://openagents.com/launch
 -Launch of OpenAgents, an AI agent swarm capable of continuous improvement through crowdsourcing and Bitcoin incentives.
 - Users can access the service through a simple chatbox on the website.
 - Currently, OpenAgents can perform basic tasks such as general conversations, introducing itself, and providing information on stocks and Bitcoin prices.
 - Developers can contribute upgrades to the agent swarm and receive Bitcoin rewards based on usage of their contributions.
 - A $1 million bounty has been allocated for developers creating the first plugins.
 - OpenAgents aims to provide a fully open alternative to existing AI platforms.
 - Key breakthroughs include building agents from reusable components, enabling them to hold Bitcoin balances, and developing a meta-agent structure for infinite extension and upgradeability.
 - User feedback is sought to guide future development efforts.
- Stacker News: open source contribution awards
 - Introducing sndev: A tool allowing users to run a full Stack Exchange Network (SN) developer environment locally in one command.
 - Developed due to struggles faced by newcomers setting up contributions to SN's open-source project and suggestions from community members.
 - Features include starting a local SN environment, logging in to local accounts, funding accounts, managing databases, and more.
 - Continuously being improved and updated; developers may use it exclusively for development purposes.
 - Contribution awards have been implemented, encouraging further involvement in the project.


